"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses Matplotlib's date functionality. When using DateFormatter and MonthLocator, the x-axis values should be dates in matplotlib's date format, not datetime objects. The code is passing datetime objects directly to set_xticks and set_xticklabels, which can cause incorrect tick labels and locations.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19c19\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n---\\n>import matplotlib.dates as mdates\\n>date_vals = mdates.date2num(df.date.unique())\\n>ax.set_xticks(date_vals)\\n20c20\\n<ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n># Removed, as DateFormatter will handle tick labels\\n\"\n}"